@ambi: I don't know what client you are using, but find in the options/preferences menu the part that has to do with queuing and set your max number of torrents to about 3 and your max number of downloads to about 2. This will speed up your transfer. The seeding goal should be at least 100% so that yo can give back to everyone once you have done downloading (also, some clients offer a ratio so the more you give, the faster you get.) Under the Bandwidth settings you choose what your system can handle (depending on if you have dial-up, DSL, Cable, etc.) Upload is normally slower than download, and if you are on a home network with other people then keep your downloads slower as well. You can usually get away with a setting of 180 Kb/s - 350 Kb/s down on DSL. On my 4G box I can go as high as 1.2Mb/s. "0" usually means "as fast as possible."
